<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Clepe" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Clepe,</orth> to call: <cit><quote>she --s him king of graves,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 995" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 995</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he --th a calf cauf,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 24</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>are clept all by the name of dogs,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 3.1.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 1, 94</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>they c. us drunkards,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 4, 19</bibl></cit>. (In Mcb. and Hml. O. Edd. <emph>clipt</emph> and <emph>clip;</emph> cf. the quibble in <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.603" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 603</bibl>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>